# Test-All Skill

Run the full test suite across every Python package, then lint. Use this before pushing to a PR.

## Step 1 — Run all Python package test suites

Run each package sequentially. Report pass/fail counts as you go.

```bash
cd packages/data      && uv run pytest tests/ -q --tb=short; cd ../..
cd packages/knowledge && uv run pytest tests/ -q --tb=short; cd ../..
cd packages/core      && uv run pytest tests/ -q --tb=short; cd ../..
cd packages/mcp-server && uv run pytest tests/ -q --tb=short; cd ../..
cd packages/cli       && uv run pytest tests/ -q --tb=short; cd ../..
```

## Step 2 — Lint

```bash
uv run ruff check . --fix
```

## Step 3 — Report

Print a summary table:

| Package   | Tests | Status |
|-----------|-------|--------|
| data      | N     | ✓ / ✗  |
| knowledge | N     | ✓ / ✗  |
| core      | N     | ✓ / ✗  |
| mcp-server| N     | ✓ / ✗  |
| cli       | N     | ✓ / ✗  |
| lint      | —     | ✓ / ✗  |

If any suite fails, print the failure output and stop — do not push.
If all suites pass, confirm it is safe to push.
